wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Thomas Coyle (25 July 1869 – 12 September 1925) was a professional cricketer, who primarily played club cricket, but also made two appearances in first-class cricket for Somerset County Cricket Club in the early twentieth century. He was a right-arm fast bowler, and continued to play professional cricket well into his forties, while also working as a sports-outfitter.
